fields.name: Africa's Finest Jollof Seasoning
fields.description: Africa's Finest Jollof Seasoning is a classic blend of delicate spices specially selected to provide a convenient way of preparing authentic Jollof Rice. There are as many ways to prepare Jollof Rice as there are cooks. The most common ingredients are rice, tomato and tomato paste, and almost any meat or vegetable can be added. Africa's finest is part of Tropical Sun Foods; Tropical Sun takes pride in providing the best products, the finest quality, at great affordable prices.

fields.name: Asun (Peppered) Goat Meat
fields.description: “Asun” is spicy grilled goat meat, cooked on the bone. Enjoy as “small chops” or add to any of our rice or beans dishes for a complete meal.

fields.name: Berbere Spice
fields.description: Berbere (Amharic: በርበሬ bärbäre, Tigrinya: በርበረ bärbärä) is a spice mixture whose constituent elements usually include chili peppers, coriander, garlic, ginger, Ethiopian holy basil (besobela) seeds, korarima, rue, ajwain or radhuni, nigella, and fenugreek. It is a key ingredient in the cuisines of Ethiopia and Eritrea.

fields.name: Diced Goat Meat 1kg
fields.description: It is naturally lean, very nutritious and has a range of health benefits. The meat has less fat, less saturated fat, more iron, and about the same amount of protein compared to beef, pork, lamb, or chicken. The overall fat content of goat meat is lower than other red meats, therefore, it provides fewer calories.

fields.name: Egusi Soup
fields.description: Creamy, nutty egusi soup is a staple in homes and bukas, or street food stalls, across Nigeria and in many parts of West Africa. The soup takes its name from egusi, or agushi―the seeds that both thicken and flavor it. Egusi soup typically features meat (such as beef, smoked poultry, goat, cow skin, and offal) and seafood (smoked dried fish or stockfish), as well as Awara (Nigerian tofu), mushrooms, and greens.

fields.name: Hot Scotch Bonnet 1kg
fields.description: Scotch bonnet (also known as Bonney peppers, or Caribbean red peppers) is a variety of chili pepper named for its supposed resemblance to a Scottish tam o' shanter bonnet] It is ubiquitous in West Africa and the Caribbean.

fields.name: Mackerel Fish 1kg
fields.description: Mackerel has a creamy and slightly salty meat that is often smoked or peppered and sold ready prepared.

fields.name: Fufu Flakes 5kg
fields.description: Fufu flakes are perfect for creating delicious and smooth potato fufu that's free from lumps. They are ideal for daily use and will help you make the tastiest potato fufu that you've ever had.

fields.name: Green Plantain
fields.description:
Plantain is a type of starchy banana that is widely used in many tropical and subtropical countries, including West Africa, the Caribbean, and South America. It is a staple food in many cultures and is used in a variety of dishes, both sweet and savory.

In terms of flavour, plantains are starchy and slightly sweet when ripe, with a slightly nutty flavour. When unripe, they have a more neutral, slightly bitter taste. The texture of plantains can be starchy and firm when unripe, and soft and sweet when ripe.

Plantains are used in a variety of dishes, from fried plantain chips to mashed plantain patties. They are often sliced and fried to make crispy chips or mashed and formed into patties for use in dishes such as plantain fritters. They can also be roasted or baked or used as a filling for tacos and other dishes.

fields.name: Hake on the bone 1kg
fields.description: Hake is a soft, white, flaky fish with a texture slightly more delicate in texture than haddock. It has a mild flavor and is lean and moist when cooked. Typical cooking methods include broiling, baking, frying, and steaming.

fields.name: Iwisi South African Maize Meal
fields.description: Maize meal, is a relatively coarse flour (much coarser than cornflour or cornstarch) made from maize or mealies in Southern Africa, from the Portuguese milho.

fields.name: Mixed Spice
fields.description:
The spice mixture is a classic blend of sweet spices and it adds a warming feeling to several dishes. The five spices work so well together and are commonly found in cakes, muffins and mince pies around Christmas.

This fantastic aromatic blend of spices is commonly found in European cuisines and cultures and it can be used in bread, pastries and cakes. The spice mix contains, cinnamon, coriander, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.

fields.name: Nigerian Amala, Ewedu and Assorted Meat
fields.description: Àmàlà can be eaten with various soups: Efo riro: made from vegetables and a mixture of meat, fish, cow skin (ponmo), and other meats. Egusi: soup made of thickened melon seeds and leaf vegetables. Ewedu soup: made from cooked and grated Corchorus leaves with or without a small quantity of egusi and/or locust beans.

fields.name: Nigerian Efo
fields.description: Efo Riro is a Yoruba word and it loosely means 'stirred spinach'. In Nigeria, the vegetables used for Efo Riro are 'Efo Shoko' (Lagos spinach) or 'Efo Tete' (African spinach). These are the local spinach varieties that are very popular and easily available. In other parts of the world, any spinach greens will do.
